==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wicker
<hw>Wick"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>wiker</ets>,
<ets>wikir</ets>, osier, probably akin to AS. <ets>w⟦imac⟧can</ets> to
give way. Cf. <er>Weak</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A small pliant twig or osier; a rod for making
basketwork and the like; a withe.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Wickerwork; a piece of wickerwork, esp. a
basket.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Then quick did dress⟦br⟧
His half milk up for cheese, and in a press⟦br⟧
Of wicker pressed it.</q> <rj><qau>Chapman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Same as 1st <er>Wike</er>.</def> <mark>[Prov.
Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wicker</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Wicker
<hw>Wick"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Made of, or covered
with, twigs or osiers, or wickerwork.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Each one a little <qex>wicker</qex> basket had,⟦br⟧
Made of fine twigs, entrail⟦eacute⟧d curiously.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wickered</ent>⟦br⟧
